#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:2
msgid "The Javascript Programming Language"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:4
msgid ""
"We have made excellent progress toward learning about Web Programming.  "
"You have learned something about two of the three primary web programming"
" languages.  We will continue to explore HTML and CSS in more detail, but"
" it is now time to turn our attention to Javascript."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:6
msgid ""
"Although we have been calling HTML and CSS programming languages, they do"
" not have nearly the power of Javascript.  Once you learn Javascript you "
"could can write any program that could be written."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:8
msgid ""
"Javascript is a procedural language.  With HTML and especially CSS the "
"order of things is not always important, but with Javascript, the order "
"that you do things in is very important.  Javascript is also called an "
"**object oriented** language.  That means that we will be working with "
"objects in our imaginary world of the browser.  Objects can tell us "
"things we want to know, and objects know how to do many things.  We only "
"need to write a javascript program to ask or tell."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:10
msgid ""
"But, lets not get caught up in a bunch of formal talk about computer "
"science and programming language theory, lets start with a simple example"
" of one of the things that Javascript is good at doing, namely making "
"buttons do interesting things.  For our first program lets make a button "
"that changes the background color of our window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:27
msgid ""
"&lt;html&gt;\n"
"   &lt;body&gt;\n"
"      &lt;h1&gt;Hello World!!&lt;/h1&gt;\n"
"      &lt;button onclick=\"changeThisPageFunc();\"&gt;Click "
"Me!&lt;/button&gt;\n"
"      &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\"&gt;\n"
"         changeThisPageFunc = function() {\n"
"            document.body.style.backgroundColor = \"lightblue\";\n"
"            document.body.innerHTML = \"&lt;h1&gt;I am a little blue "
"today&lt;/h1&gt;\";\n"
"         }\n"
"      &lt;/script&gt;\n"
"   &lt;/body&gt;\n"
"&lt;/html&gt;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:28
msgid ""
"Now that example may look very complex to you, and in fact it does "
"demonstrate **LOTS** of important aspects of programming.  But do not "
"worry, we'll dissect this example carefully so that you fully understand "
"what is going on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:30
msgid "Here are some questions that we should answer about the example above:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:32
msgid ""
"Button?  We haven't talked about a ``button`` tag before, whats the deal "
"with that?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:33
msgid "What is the ``onclick`` attribute for?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:34
msgid "script tag?  Again this is a new one why a ``script`` tag?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:35
msgid "What in the world does all of that stuff inside the script tag mean?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:36
msgid "What happened to my button!?!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:38
msgid ""
"Those are all very good questions, I'm glad you asked.  Lets take them "
"one at a time right now, and then we'll expand upon the ideas in the next"
" few sections."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:40
msgid ""
"The button tag is part of HTML that is going to allow us to make "
"interactive websites.  In addition to buttons there are other things like"
" check boxes, and text input, that we will talk about in the next "
"section.  For now we will use the button as a simple example, of "
"something we are all used to using every day."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:42
msgid ""
"The ``onclick`` attribute is the way we answer the question, \"what "
"should this button do when someone clicks on it.\"  The answer in this "
"case is may lead to confusion, but hopefully you at least get the idea "
"that when the button is clicked we want to \"change this page\".  The way"
" we are going to do this is through a **function call**. You have used "
"functions in math class many times, and these are not all that different."
"  The important thing to remember is that functions are **abstractions** "
"of things that need doing.  We all use abstractions all the time in our "
"everyday life."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:44
msgid ""
"For example, you may tell your friend, \"I'm going to Computer Science "
"now.\" this is an abstraction of the following hypothetical steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:46
msgid "Get out of bed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:47
msgid "Get dressed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:48
msgid "Walk out of your room, down the hall and wait for the elevator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:49
msgid "Take the elevator to the fourth floor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:50
msgid "Walk out of the elevator, out of the door, and across campus to Olin hall."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:51
msgid ""
"Go in the door, and up the stairs to second floor, enter room 202 and "
"find your favorite place to sit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:53
msgid ""
"That would be a long boring conversation if you responded with all 6 of "
"those steps every time a friend asked you what you were doing. But your "
"friend understands those steps are necessary when you say you are going "
"to class.   Further more even step 1 is an abstraction of several smaller"
" steps:  Sit up, remove the covers, slide my legs over the side of the "
"bed, stand up (or climb down the ladder)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:55
msgid ""
"This brings us to the next question, the ``script`` tag is one way that "
"we can include Javascript in our HTML.  But like CSS we will see that we "
"can, and should, also include Javascript by putting it in its own file "
"and including it.  More on that later."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:57
msgid ""
"The stuff inside the script tag is Javascript code. This code contains a "
"**function definition** which is how we create our very own abstractions."
" Unlike your friend to naturally understands what it means to go to "
"class, computers are very dumb, and very literal, they only do what you "
"tell them.  In this case there are two steps to our abstraction.  One "
"changes the background color of the body, and the second one changes our "
"message.  These lines are also abstractions of a very complicated set of "
"steps that we as programmers don't need to know the details of right now."
"  We just need to know which abstractions the browser understands."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_sources/Javascript/intro.rst:59
msgid ""
"Lets defer the question of what happened to the button for just a bit.  "
"In the meantime experiment with the Javascript code by trying the "
"following things:"
msgstr ""

